==English==
===Etymology===
Invented by Shakespeare in ''Macbeth'' - ''What, all my pretty chickens and their dam At one fell swoop?'' ([[fell]] meaning [[fierce]])
===Noun===
'''[[one]] [[fell]] [[swoop]]'''
#{{idiom}} One [[stroke]]; one [[action]] or [[event]] with many results.
#:''Changing the oil lubricates the engine and removes debris in '''one fell swoop'''.''

